Time Model Statistics

  • DB Time represents total time in user calls
  • DB CPU represents CPU time of foreground processes
  • Total CPU Time represents foreground and background processes
  • Statistics including the word "background" measure background process time, therefore do not contribute to the DB time statistic
  • Ordered by % of DB time in descending order, followed by Statistic Name

Impact is .14 active sessions, 3.97% of total activity.

of literals.

Related Object
SQL statement with SQL_ID 0pmk5768w2w42.
select
dos."ID" as DOSSIER_ID
, dos."KEY"
, dos.AFG_BSN
, dos.UZS_VOLGNUMMER
, nvl(dos."COOKBOOKFK",dos."KEY") as COOKBOOKFK
, dos."COOKBOOKVALUEFK"
, dos."VALUE"
, dosdat.DATUM_ANTWOORD
, case when ref.VERVANGENDE_WAARDE_IND = 'Ja'
then 'Gevuld'
when dos."KEY" = 'gender' and dos."VALUE" = 'F'
then 'Vrouw'
when dos."KEY" = 'gender' and dos."VALUE" = 'M'
then 'Man'
when dos."KEY" = 'gender'
then 'Gender neutraal'
when dos."KEY" is not NULL
then dos."VALUE"
when dos."COOKBOOKVALUEFK" is not NULL
then cook."TITEL"
else dos."VALUE"
end as ANTWOORD
, dos."SEQUENCE" as ANTWOORD_VOLGNUMMER
, dos.DIM_START_DATUM
, dos.DIM_EIND_DATUM
, dos.DIM_RECENT_IND
, dos.DIM_ARCHIEFVERNIETIGING_STATUS
from OKV_PEERCODE_PO.OKV_PEER_DOSSIER_HV dos
inner join
(
select
"ID" as DOSSIER_ID
, UZS_VOLGNUMMER
, AFG_BSN
, TRUNC(TO_TIMESTAMP("VALUE",'YYYY-MM-DD HH24:MI:SS')) as
DATUM_ANTWOORD
from OKV_PEERCODE_PO.OKV_PEER_DOSSIER_HV
where "KEY" = 'response_at'
) dosdat
on dos."ID" = dosdat.DOSSIER_ID
and dos.UZS_VOLGNUMMER = dosdat.UZS_VOLGNUMMER
and dos.AFG_BSN = dosdat.AFG_BSN
left join
(
select
UUID as COOKBOOKVALUEFK
, "TITEL"
from OKV_PEERCODE_PO.OKV_PEER_COOKBOOK_HV
) cook
on dos.COOKBOOKVALUEFK = cook.COOKBOOKVALUEFK
left join
(
select
nvl(COOKBOOK_UUID, DOSSIER_KEY) as COOKBOOKFK
, VERVANGENDE_WAARDE_IND
from INT_PEER_PO.REF_PEER_TB
where COOKBOOK_UUID is not NULL
) ref
on nvl(dos."COOKBOOKFK",dos."KEY") = ref.COOKBOOKFK

Finding 2: Undersized SGA
Impact is .75 active sessions, 27.07% of total activity.
--------------------------------------------------------
The SGA was inadequately sized, causing additional I/O or hard parses.
The value of parameter "sga_target" was "40960 M" during the analysis period.

Recommendation 1: Database Configuration
Estimated benefit is .76 active sessions, 27.07% of total activity.
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Action
Increase the size of the SGA by setting the parameter "sga_target" to
51200 M.

Symptoms That Led to the Finding:
---------------------------------
Wait class "User I/O" was consuming significant database time.
Impact is .79 active sessions, 28.19% of total activity.
